---
import Badge from "@/components/ui/badge.astro";
import Header from "@/components/Header.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import alexis from "../assets/alexis.jpg";
import mountain from "../assets/mountain.jpg";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <main
    class="w-full flex flex-col items-center max-w-[1150px] mx-auto pt-4 gap-12 px-4"
  >
    <section
      class="w-full pt-24 sm:pt-28 p-3 flex flex-col gap-8 pb-8 animate-in fade-in duration-1000 fill-mode-backwards"
    >
      <div class="space-y-4 text-center">
        <div class="text-4xl sm:text-6xl font-medium max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Travel should be about experiences, not spreadsheets.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="text-lg text-muted-foreground max-w-xl mx-auto text-center">
        I built Tracktrip because I was tired of losing track of my spending
        while traveling.
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="w-full h-[400px] overflow-hidden rounded shrink-0">
      <Image
        src={mountain}
        alt="Mountain"
        class="object-cover"
        width="1400"
        height="400"
        decoding="async"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>

    <section
      class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-between w-full gap-12 px-1 sm:px-8"
    >
      <div class="w-full sm:w-1/2 space-y-6 text-xl font-medium">
        It all started while traveling
      </div>
      <div class="w-full sm:w-1/2 space-y-6 text-sm">
        <div>
          On a train from Stockholm to Narvik, I realized I had no idea how much
          Iâ€™d spent that week. Receipts were lost, currencies were confusing,
          and my bank app only showed half the picture. I needed a tool built
          for travelers, by a traveler.
        </div>
        <div>
          Most budgeting apps are designed for daily life, not for the chaos of
          travel. They donâ€™t account for multiple currencies, shared expenses,
          or the spontaneity of being on the road.
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section
      class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-between w-full gap-12 px-1 sm:px-8"
    >
      <div class="w-full sm:w-1/2 space-y-6 text-xl font-medium">
        A tool for travelers, by a traveler
      </div>
      <div class="w-full sm:w-1/2 space-y-6 text-sm">
        <div>
          I developed Tracktrip as a personal project during my travels, using
          it to manage my own expenses across multiple countries. It became an
          essential tool for me, helping me stay on budget and understand my
          spending patterns.
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section
      class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-between w-full gap-12 px-1 sm:px-8"
    >
      <div class="w-full sm:w-1/2 space-y-6 text-xl font-medium">
        Open-sourcing Tracktrip
      </div>
      <div class="w-full sm:w-1/2 space-y-6 text-sm">
        <div>
          After seeing how useful it was for my own travels, I decided to
          open-source Tracktrip so that others could benefit from it as well.
          Now, anyone can use and contribute to the project, making travel
          budgeting easier for everyone.
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="w-full p-6 border rounded-lg mt-6">
      <div class="w-full flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center gap-4">
        <div
          class="h-[220px] w-full sm:w-[220px] overflow-hidden rounded shrink-0 flex justify-center"
        >
          <Image src={alexis} alt="Alexis" class="object-cover" />
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl sm:mb-10 font-medium">About me</div>
          <div
            class="font-medium uppercase font-mono text-subtle-foreground text-sm"
          >
            Alexis
          </div>
          <div class="text-base mt-2">
            ðŸ‘‹ I love to travel. I've traveled in Europe for 6 months, and
            that's when I decided to build Tracktrip. I wanted a better way to
            track my expenses and stay on budget while exploring new places.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="w-full text-center py-12">
      <div class="text-muted-foreground max-w-xl mx-auto font-light">
        Travel is about freedom. Tracktrip gives you the freedom to spend
        wisely, so you can focus on what matters.
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
